¦ The Comparable interface allows classes to be compared.
¦ This interface extends from the Equatable interface.
¦ @author Vincent Philippe (@vincent64)
¦ @version 0.1
¦
interface+ Comparable(Equatable) {

    ¦ Returns whether the current object is greater than the given object.
    ¦ @param object the object
    ¦ @returns true if the current object is greater
    ¦
    op bool >(Object object);

    ¦ Returns whether the current object is less than the given object.
    ¦ @param object the object
    ¦ @returns true if the current object is less
    ¦
    op bool <(Object object);

    ¦ Returns whether the current object is greater or equal than the given object.
    ¦ @param object the object
    ¦ @returns true if the current object is greater or equal
    ¦
    op bool >=(Object object);

    ¦ Returns whether the current object is less or equal than the given object.
    ¦ @param object the object
    ¦ @returns true if the current object is less or equal
    ¦
    op bool <=(Object object);

    ¦ Compares the current object with the given object, and returns an integer-based
    ¦ value according to the comparison.
    ¦ @param object the object
    ¦ @returns 1 if the current object is greater than the other;
    ¦          0 if the objects are equal;
    ¦          -1 if the current object is less than the other
    ¦
    op int <=>(Object object);
